EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Introduction be Approved by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the date of issuance and publication by the Mayor of a ten-year capital strategy, the date of submission by the Mayor of the proposed executive budget and budget message, the date of submission by the Borough Presidents of recommendations in response to the Mayor’s executive budget, the date of publication of a report by the director of the independent budget office analyzing the executive budget, the date by which the Council hearings pertaining to the executive budget shall conclude, the date by which if the expense budget has not been adopted, the expense budget and tax rate adopted as modified for the current fiscal year shall be deemed to have been extended for the new fiscal year until such time as a new expense budget has been adopted, the date by which if a capital budget and a capital program have not been adopted, the unutilized portion of all prior capital appropriations shall be deemed reappropriated, the date of submission by the Mayor of an estimate of the probable amount of receipts, the date by which any person or organization may submit an official alternative estimate of revenues, the date by which if the Council has not fixed the tax rates for the ensuing fiscal year, the commissioner of finance shall be authorized to complete the assessment rolls using estimated rates, and related matters, relating to the fiscal year two thousand fourteen.

INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to enact and the President to sign the Flood Victim Premium Relief Act of 2013.
EventItemMatterName: Flood Victim Premium Relief Act of 2013.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the State of New York to make active the Amistad Commission and promote a curriculum, such as the Underground Railroad curriculum, that teaches African-American history in New York public schools.
EventItemMatterName: Make active the Amistad Commission and promote a curriculum, such as the Underground Railroad curriculum, that teaches African-American history in NY public schools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the display of commuter van information.
EventItemMatterName: Display of commuter van information.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation requiring intercity buses to visibly identify the destination, operator, and operator’s contact information on the exterior of each bus.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring intercity buses to visibly identify the destination, operator, and operator’s contact information on the exterior of each bus.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to requiring the commissioner of the department of correction to post a monthly report on its website regarding punitive segregation, including solitary confinement, statistics for city jails.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the commissioner of the department of correction to post a monthly report on its website regarding punitive segregation, including solitary confinement, statistics for city jails.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Department of Correction to end the practice of placing individuals returning to City jails into punitive segregation, also known as solitary confinement, to complete time owed.
EventItemMatterName: Dept of Correction to end the practice of placing individuals returning to City jails into punitive segregation to complete time owed.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign a comprehensive immigration reform bill in 2013.
EventItemMatterName: Comprehensive immigration reform bill in 2013.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Assembly and New York State Senate to pass and the Governor to sign A.3339, which would amend the New York State Penal Law to redefine rape as criminal sexual conduct.
EventItemMatterName: Redefine rape as criminal sexual conduct. (A.3339)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A5470, which would amend the Vehicle and Traffic Law in relation to extending the period for the repair of defective equipment on the basis of religious observance.
EventItemMatterName: Extending the period for the repair of defective equipment on the basis of religious observance. (A.5470)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the enforcement of motor scooter provisions.
EventItemMatterName: Enforcement of motor scooter provisions.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating designated mobile food truck locations.
EventItemMatterName: Creating designated mobile food truck locations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to transfer of muni-meter time.
EventItemMatterName: Transfer of muni-meter time.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the establishment of an M/WBE advisory board.
EventItemMatterName: Establishment of an M/WBE advisory board.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would require local legislative approval prior to the siting of commercial casinos.
EventItemMatterName: Require local legislative approval prior to the siting of commercial casinos.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Department of Agriculture to make undocumented immigrants eligible for the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program.
EventItemMatterName: US Dept of Agriculture to make undocumented immigrants eligible for the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the requirement of food vendors to obtain a certificate of authority to collect sales tax.
EventItemMatterName: Requirement of food vendors to obtain a certificate of authority to collect sales tax.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the federal government to simplify tax filing for same-sex married couples.
EventItemMatterName: Calling on the federal government to simplify tax filing for same-sex married couples.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the prohibition of motor scooter use by businesses.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibition of motor scooter use by businesses.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Congress of the United States to pass, the President of the United States to sign, and a three-fourths majority of the States to ratify the Equal Rights Amendment.
EventItemMatterName: A three-fourths majority of the States to ratify the Equal Rights Amendment.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of a registry of transportation providers for adult day care programs.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a registry of transportation providers for adult day care programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Housing
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Housing Authority to meaningfully engage residents on proposed lease plans, to provide predominantly and permanently affordable units and to include certain requirements in any ground leases for NYCHA land.
EventItemMatterName: NYCHA to meaningfully engage residents on proposed lease plans, to provide predominantly and permanently affordable units and to include certain requirements in any ground leases for NYCHA land.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance

EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of the CAMPUS Safety Act of 2013 (H.R.359/S.433), which would establish and operate a National Center for Campus Public Safety.
EventItemMatterName: CAMPUS Safety Act of 2013 (H.R.359/S.433)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to introduce and pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would allow a tax credit to property owners who install surveillance cameras on their property.
EventItemMatterName: Allow a tax credit to property owners who install surveillance cameras on their property.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the corporation counsel to submit quarterly reports to the city council.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the corporation counsel to submit quarterly reports to the city council.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to door to door commercial solicitations.
EventItemMatterName: Door to door commercial solicitations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that amends the Padavan law to provide meaningful guidance on what would be considered such a concentration of community residential facilities that the nature and character of an area would be substantially altered.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Padavan law to provide meaningful guidance on what would be considered such a concentration of community residential facilities that the nature and character of an area would be substantially altered.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to require police departments to provide certain security measures for nonpublic schools.
EventItemMatterName: Require police departments to provide certain security measures for nonpublic schools.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the mandatory revocation of an amusement arcade or gaming cafe license for offering cash prizes or engaging in other unlawful gambling activity.
EventItemMatterName: Mandatory revocation of an amusement arcade or gaming cafe license for offering cash prizes or engaging in other unlawful gambling activity.
